data.description: This three bedroom, two bath home of almost 1,700 square feet sits nicely off of Skipper Road in the Rehobeth area, situated on over three quarters of an acre. Built in 2019, the home is like new, with neutral colors and attractive finishings. The floor plan is open, with vinyl plank flooring in the living room, dining area and kitchen. The kitchen features an eat-at bar, with granite countertops, a white subway tile backsplash, stainless appliances and a corner pantry. Behind the kitchen is a spacious laundry room with built-in cabinets with access to the carport area. The split bedroom floor plan places the primary bedroom on the left side of the home, a spacious room with three windows. The ensuite bath includes dual sinks set in a long granite-topped vanity, a walk-in closet, and a soaking tub and shower framed in horizontal tiles below a transom window. The spare bedrooms and full guest bath are situated on the opposite side of the home. There is plenty of personal space in the backyard, with part of the yard fenced with wire fencing on the sides and decorative, white farm-style fencing facing the road. The covered patio area adjacent to the attached carport creates an ideal space for entertaining outdoors!
